Literally everything you listed are one sided from actresses who felt uncomfortable with him, but we never got his side except that one interview.
Certainly, he was not being transparent with those women and was not considerate of their feelings and made them uncomfortable, no one can deny that.
Okay, so his "direction" or productions tends to fall more in line with things that may sexualize women, but maybe that's just his artistic preference?
The main point these women are saying of what's bad about this is how he "storms out" and gets frustrated when they decline. Yeah, so what?
Was he violent or continued to harass or force them to do anything? Hell no. It's understandable he got frustrated because he had set up productions.
That said, as I said, it is also his fault for not being transparent with them and honestly, it does come across as creepy and weird, but that's not enough to cancel him over.
